"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-272","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":25400,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/11\/09\/combine-salat-traveling\/","url_meta":{"origin":8124,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Travel: The Prophet combined prayers during travel","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 9, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, combined sunset and evening\u00a0prayers if he was undertaking a journey. And Ibn Abbas said, \u201cThe Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, combined the noon prayers and afternoon prayers\u00a0if he was on a journey, as well as\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":8150,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/14\/fifty-salat-five-a-day\/","url_meta":{"origin":8124,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Salat: Fifty prayers reduces to five prayers a day","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 14, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: Allah commanded your Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, to perform fifty prayers in a day. Then, the Prophet asked his Lord Almighty about it, so Allah made them five prayers in a day. Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 2885 Grade:\u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according to Ahmad Shakir \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u064e\u0651\u0627\u0633\u064d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25413,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/11\/13\/shorten-prayers-travel\/","url_meta":{"origin":8124,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Travel: Permission to shorten prayers during travel","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 13, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: We went out with the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, from Medina to Mecca and he would pray two cycles\u00a0at a time until he returned. Yahya ibn Abi Ishaq said, \u201cHow long did he remain in Mecca?\u201d Anas said, \u201cTen days.\u201d Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19348,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/06\/17\/prophet-lightens-salat-for-child\/","url_meta":{"origin":8124,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Ease: The Prophet lightens prayer on occasion","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 17, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, I might\u00a0begin the prayer and I intend to prolong it, but then I hear the crying of an infant. I will\u00a0shorten the prayer as\u00a0I know his crying will distress his mother.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 710, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":22643,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/04\/17\/istighfar-relief-rizq\/","url_meta":{"origin":8124,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Istighfar: Seeking forgiveness rewarded with relief, provision","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 17, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever increases his prayers for forgiveness, Allah will grant him relief from every worry, a way out from every hardship, and provide for him in ways he does not expect.\u201d Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 2234 Grade: Sahih\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25415,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/11\/13\/salat-shortened-two-rakaat-travel\/","url_meta":{"origin":8124,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Travel: Prayer shortened to two cycles during travel","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 13, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: I accompanied the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and during travel he would not add more to his prayer than two cycles. Abu Bakr, Umar, and Uthman did likewise, may Allah be pleased with them. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1051, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 689 Grade:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/8124","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=8124"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/8124\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=8124"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=8124"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=8124"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}